\ T60 INTERACTIVE: capture the top button, then GREEN once it has been pressed.
\ The button MUST be captured first (write 1 to addr 0x1a via `set`) or presses go
\ to the robot's default handler and never reach the program -- that was why the
\ earlier version never lit. Ground truth: OzoBlockly's "capture button press =
\ true" block compiles to `1 26 set` (captured + disassembled from a real flash).
evo
TRUE BUTTON_CAPTURE set
forever
  EV_BUTTON checkEvent 0 >  if 0 127 0 led then
  20 wait
loop
